## Try→Test→Fix Loop Template

For each phase above, the loop is:

```
for each test T1..T5:
  result = call_proxy(tool, input)
  assert expected_behavior(result)
  if FAIL:
    log diff(expected, actual)
    patch proxy handler for tool
    re-run T1..T5 from start
  else:
    mark test PASS
advance to next phase only when ALL tests in current phase = PASS
```

Key proxy-level invariants to check on **every** tool call: [simonwillison](https://simonwillison.net/2025/Nov/9/gpt-5-codex-mini/)
- Response uses `Responses API` format (`output[]` array), not Chat Completions `choices[]`
- `instructions` key must be present in every request — the ChatGPT backend **rejects requests without it** [simonwillison](https://simonwillison.net/2025/Nov/9/gpt-5-codex-mini/)
- `reasoning.summary: "auto"` must be included for models that use extended reasoning
- `parallel_tool_calls: true` (or false) respected per turn 